The `findStreetByIntersections` function in the [`plsql.sql`](plsql.sql#L650-L682) file takes a string as input and returns a string array. The string input represents a street name, and the function returns all the intersections that this street has with other streets.

This function is called from the Java application in the `Find` class located at [`src/main/java/org/example/DAO/Find.java`](src/main/java/org/example/DAO/Find.java#L72-L96). 

Here's how it works:

```type:Quoted,lang:Java,path:src/main/java/org/example/DAO/Find.java,lines:72-96
public static void findStreetByIntersections(Connection connection) throws SQLException{
        System.out.println("Street name: ");
        String name = scanner.nextLine();

        CallableStatement callableStatement = connection.prepareCall("begin ? := findStreetByIntersections(?); end;");
        callableStatement.registerOutParameter(1, OracleTypes.ARRAY, "STRING_ARRAY");
        callableStatement.setString(2, name);
        callableStatement.execute();

        Array result = callableStatement.getArray(1);

        Object obj = result.getArray();

        Object [] objectArray = (Object []) obj;   // cast it to an array of objects

        StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer("");
        buffer.append(String.valueOf(objectArray[0]));
        for (int j = 1; j &lt; objectArray.length; j++)
        {
            buffer.append("\n").append(String.valueOf(objectArray[j]));
        }
        System.out.println(buffer);
    }
```


In the Java application, it prompts the user to enter a street name. It then constructs a `CallableStatement` to call the `findStreetByIntersections` PL/SQL function with the entered street name as a parameter. The `callableStatement.execute()` call executes the function.

The function will return an array of intersections as an Oracle Array object. This object is then transformed into a plain Java array using the `result.getArray()` function. This plain array is then printed out as a list of strings. Each string represents an intersection that the entered street has with other streets.

